properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 29 at 2:14PM MST until March 2 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW AT TIMES WILL IMPACT AREAS ALONG AND
WEST OF THE LARAMIE RANGE SUNDAY THROUGH MONDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Snow expected with periods of blowing snow. Total snow
accumulations of 4 to 7 inches with locally higher amounts near
the mountains. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Central Carbon County, including Rawlins and Sinclair.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Sunday to 5 AM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Transportation may be severely impacted with snow
covered roads...drifting snow and poor visibility. Plan on
slippery road conditions. Periods of blowing snow possible
Sunday afternoon through early Sunday evening.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM SUNDAY TO 5 AM MST MONDAY
